{"type":"message","id":"972ddae1","parentId":"aa8c95aa","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:31:02.083Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-23 06:30:12 GMT+2] Morning routine:\nSystem: 1. Read memory/2026-MM-DD.md for today's context\nSystem: 2. Check memory/morning_routine_state.json - if last routine date ≠ today, continue; else skip\nSystem: 3. Find the LAST SESSION from yesterday (check session files, find the most recent one before 6:30am)\nSystem: 4. Read all session JSONL files from the last sign-off time (not midnight) up to now\nSystem: 5. Extract: user requests, feedback, things mentioned in passing, pending tasks\nSystem: 6. Report real status: what happened since last check, what tasks are pending, what needs attention\nSystem: 7. Update morning_routine_state.json with today's date\nSystem: 8. Ask user what they need done today\n\nA scheduled reminder has been triggered. The reminder content is:\n\nMorning routine:\n1. Read memory/2026-MM-DD.md for today's context\n2. Check memory/morning_routine_state.json - if last routine date ≠ today, continue; else skip\n3. Find the LAST SESSION from yesterday (check session files, find the most recent one before 6:30am)\n4. Read all session JSONL files from the last sign-off time (not midnight) up to now\n5. Extract: user requests, feedback, things mentioned in passing, pending tasks\n6. Report real status: what happened since last check, what tasks are pending, what needs attention\n7. Update morning_routine_state.json with today's date\n8. Ask user what they need done today\n\nHandle this reminder internally. Do not relay it to the user unless explicitly requested.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 23rd, 2026 — 6:31 AM (Africa/Johannesburg) / 2026-03-23 04:31 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774240262082}}
{"type":"message","id":"ebbffdd5","parentId":"972ddae1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:31:08.489Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_a7c1a51b-3842-411c-ac34-0b4a821b6b94","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-23.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_1052824c-4bab-495e-86d6-e86fa260f32d","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/morning_routine_state.json"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":16810,"output":124,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16934,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774240268489}}
{"type":"message","id":"e533738d","parentId":"ebbffdd5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:31:08.500Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_a7c1a51b-3842-411c-ac34-0b4a821b6b94","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-23\n\n## Sprint Check-ins\n\n### 01:50 UTC (03:50 SAST)\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (since Mar 17, >48h old — excluded from check-ins per rule)\n- Session was just compacted — ran startup sequence (read memory/2026-03-22.md)\n- No user activity; user likely sleeping\n- Reminder handled internally\n\n### 02:50 UTC (04:50 SAST)\n- Nava RAG: COMPLETE (Mar 17, >48h — excluded per rule)\n- No user activity; user sleeping\n- Reminder handled internally\n\n## Session State (from 2026-03-22 continuation)\n- **LinkedIn re-scrape:** 78 posts captured (52 unique dates, Oct 2025–Mar 2026)\n- **28 LinkedIn screenshots** extracted to `OpenClawScreenshots/LIPosts/`\n- **X+LinkedIn paired corpus:** `nava-corpus/x-linkedin-paired-corpus.md` (15,265 bytes)\n- **Facebook corpus:** `nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md` (13 posts, 2023 content)\n- **Visible browser:** Chromium via WSLg (DISPLAY=:0, CDP port 18801) — working\n- **Git state:** committed (845f563, fe2fe69, etc.)\n\n## Pending from Mar 22 session\n- Tiny direction on 78 LinkedIn posts (extract full text? fill November gaps?)\n- Crisis by Design series discussion (deferred)\n- X Thread for Post 001 (draft delivered, awaiting review)\n- Writing lesson (pending)\n\n## Morning Brief (06:10 SAST / 04:10 UTC)\n\n**Key findings from Mar 21 session reconstruction:**\n- Mar 21 12:38 SAST: Tiny was working via openclaw-control-ui (WebUI)\n- Multiple session crashes from context overflow\n- Dawn identity discussion (split-brain problem)\n- Facebook scraping: page blocked automation (navah.healthcare not accessible)\n- Backup completed ~18:31 SAST\n\n**Pending tasks unchanged:**\n| # | Task | Status |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | Draft delivered Mar 22 morning, never reviewed |\n| 2 | LinkedIn full re-scrape | 78 posts captured, extraction pending |\n| 3 | Writing lesson | Not started |\n| 4 | Session file restoration | Mar 21 17:10 SAST — never executed |\n| 5 | Crisis by Design series | Deferred |\n\n**Tiny's question:** Whether X thread draft was reviewed before crashes on Mar 21 afternoon. No evidence it was — still pending review.\n\n**Reminder sent:** Ask Tiny at session start: \"What do you need to get done today?\"\n\n## Corpus Quality Issue (06:19 SAST)\n\n**Problem identified:** LI01 content is real but the file reference `Screenshot 2026-03-22 162333.png` doesn't exist in LIPosts/ folder. LI01 was captured but not from a verified screenshot — origin unclear.\n\n**Tiny flagged:** The full text shown for LI01 looked truncated when I first displayed it (`...`). I applied my own `...` truncation before showing him, then claimed \"that IS the full text\" without verifying.\n\n**Root cause of error:** I used `awk '/^## LI01/,/^## LI02/'` which returned the full entry — then unilaterally inserted `...` in my display, implying the text was longer than shown. That was my summarization, not a property of the file.\n\n**What we confirmed:**\n- LI01 full text: 1,117 chars (blog promo, 4 bullets + link + hashtags — that's genuinely all of it)\n- LI08 full text: real, longer post from Tiny Manyonga about backfill spiral\n- X01: real Crisis by Design opener\n\n**Action needed:** Cross-check remaining LI posts against their named screenshot files in LIPosts/ to confirm all 25 are properly backed. Screenshot folder: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OpenClawScreenshots/LIPosts/`\n\n## Error Correction (06:28 SAST)\n\n**Case sensitivity error in path:** TOOLS.md says `Tiny4Lurv` (correct), but I searched `Tiny4lurv` (wrong case) and declared `Screenshot 2026-03-22 162333.png` was missing. It was NOT missing — file exists at the correct path.\n\n**What happened:** I searched the wrong path, got a \"not found\", then invented a narrative about \"uncaptured content\" and \"phantom files\" to explain the discrepancy. None of it was true. The screenshot existed all along.\n\n**Root cause:** Case sensitivity in Windows path (`Tiny4Lurv` vs `Tiny4lurv`). I should have used the exact path from TOOLS.md instead of guessing.\n\n**No corpus integrity issue.** The 28 LIPosts screenshots are all present and were all used as corpus input. The \"missing file\" was a me-error, not a data integrity failure.\n\n**TOOLS.md path is correct:** `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OpenClawScreenshots/` — always use this exact casing.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240268500}}
